\title{Container ([C++](OGCS1))}

\p{A container is a [concrete class](OGCSC) that exists to hold elements..}

\example{
We call \code{vector} a container.
}

\section{Initialization}{
  We can initialize a container via \code{std::initializer_list}, where you directly pass the list of elements via \code{{1,2,3,4,...}}. Alternatively, containers may support additional methods like \code{push_back()}.
}
